5
6 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; amending 68
O.S. 2021, Section 3634, which relates to the Filmed
7 in Oklahoma Act of 2021; modifying provisions related
to expenditure requirements for incentive
8 eligibility; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3634, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 3634. A. The total amount of rebate payments
15 conditionally pre-qualified by the Department of Commerce each
16 fiscal year with respect to any of the incentives authorized
17 pursuant to this act shall not exceed Thirty Million Dollars
18 ($30,000,000.00). Projects not conditionally pre-qualified for
19 rebate payments due to the limitations provided in this section may
20 be conditionally pre-qualified by the Department in subsequent
21 fiscal years.
22 B. The amount of rebate payments conditionally pre-qualified by
23 the Department of Commerce each fiscal year with respect to any of
24 the incentives authorized pursuant to this act shall not exceed:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4215 Page 1

1 1. Seven Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($7,500,000.00)
2 for production projects with total expenditures of less than Seven
3 Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($7,500,000.00); and
4 2. Twenty-two Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
5 ($22,500,000.00) for production projects with total expenditures of
6 Seven Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($7,500,000.00) or more.
7 C. A production project shall have total expenditures of Fifty
8 Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00) or more to be eligible for the rebate
9 payments provided in this act or Twenty Thousand Dollars
10 ($20,000.00) for projects filmed outside this state as provided for
11 in Section 3636 of this title.
12 D. In any fiscal year if the amount of rebate payments
13 conditionally pre-qualified by the Department of Commerce are less
14 than the limitations provided in this section, the excess rebate
15 payments not utilized shall be added to subsequent fiscal year's
16 limitation.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
